### Analysis of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 4 building blocks arranged in a single layer.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
  - A red arch-shaped block forms the base.
  - Two yellow dome-shaped blocks are placed side by side on top of the arch.
  - An orange triangular block is positioned on top of the domes.

### Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

- **Block Indices:**
  - Red Arch: Index 1
  - Yellow Dome: Index 6
  - Orange Triangle: Index 15

### Assembly Order:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 1 (Red Arch)
   Step2: Move block with index 6 (Yellow Dome) to the left position on top of the arch
   Step3: Move block with index 6 (Yellow Dome) to the right position on top of the arch
   Step4: Move block with index 15 (Orange Triangle) to the top position
}
